#. type: Title =
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Handling login and registration endpoints yourself"
msgstr "Lidando com endpoints de login e registro por conta própria"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sometimes, you will want to ask for more data than just a username in order to register a user,\n"
"or you want to deal with login and registration with custom validation, and so the default WebAuthn login\n"
"and registration endpoints are not enough."
msgstr "Às vezes, você desejará solicitar mais dados do que apenas um nome de usuário para registrar um usuário, ou deseja lidar com o login e o registro com validação personalizada, e por isso os endpoints padrão de login e registro do WebAuthn não são suficientes."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In this case, you can use the `WebAuthn.loginClientSteps` and `WebAuthn.registerClientSteps` methods from the JavaScript\n"
"library, store the authenticator data in hidden form elements, and send them as part of your form payload\n"
"to the server to your custom login or registration endpoints."
msgstr "Neste caso, você pode usar os métodos `WebAuthn.loginClientSteps` e `WebAuthn.registerClientSteps` da biblioteca JavaScript, armazenar os dados do autenticador em elementos de formulário ocultos e enviá-los como parte do payload do seu formulário para o servidor em seus endpoints de login ou registro personalizados."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you are storing them in form input elements, you can then use the link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnLoginResponse.html[`WebAuthnLoginResponse`] and\n"
"link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnRegistrationResponse.html[`WebAuthnRegistrationResponse`] classes,\n"
"mark them as `@BeanParam` and then use the\n"
"link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#login(io.quarkus.security.webauthn.WebAuthnLoginResponse,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.login`]\n"
"and link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#register(io.quarkus.security.webauthn.WebAuthnRegisterResponse,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.register`]\n"
"methods to replace the `/q/webauthn/login` and `/q/webauthn/register` endpoints."
msgstr "Se você estiver armazenando-os em elementos de input de formulário, poderá usar as classes link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnLoginResponse.html[`WebAuthnLoginResponse`] e link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnRegistrationResponse.html[`WebAuthnRegistrationResponse`], marcá-las como `@BeanParam` e então usar os métodos link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#login(io.quarkus.security.webauthn.WebAuthnLoginResponse,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.login`] e link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#register(io.quarkus.security.webauthn.WebAuthnRegisterResponse,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.register`] para substituir os endpoints `/q/webauthn/login` e `/q/webauthn/register`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In most cases you can keep using the `/q/webauthn/login-options-challenge` and `/q/webauthn/register-options-challenge` challenge-initiating\n"
"endpoints, because this is not where custom logic is required."
msgstr "Na maioria dos casos, você pode continuar usando os endpoints iniciadores de desafio `/q/webauthn/login-options-challenge` e `/q/webauthn/register-options-challenge`, pois não é neles que a lógica personalizada é necessária."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In this case, the registration flow is a little different because you will write your own registration endpoint\n"
"which will handle storing of the credentials and setting up the session cookie:"
msgstr "Neste caso, o fluxo de registro é um pouco diferente porque você escreverá seu próprio endpoint de registro que lidará com o armazenamento das credenciais e a configuração do cookie de sessão:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Similarly, the login flow is a little different because you will write your own login endpoint\n"
"which will handle updating the credentials and setting up the session cookie:"
msgstr "Da mesma forma, o fluxo de login é um pouco diferente porque você escreverá seu próprio endpoint de login que lidará com a atualização das credenciais e a configuração do cookie de sessão:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you handle user and credential creation and logins yourself in your endpoints, you only need\n"
"to provide a read-only view of your entities in your link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`], so you can skip\n"
"the `store` and `update` methods:"
msgstr "Se você mesmo lidar com a criação de usuários e credenciais e logins em seus endpoints, precisará apenas fornecer uma visão somente leitura de suas entidades no seu link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`], podendo assim pular os métodos `store` e `update`:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When setting up your own login and registration endpoints, you don't need to enable the default endpoints, so you can\n"
"remove the `quarkus.webauthn.enable-login-endpoint` and `quarkus.webauthn.enable-registration-endpoint` configuration."
msgstr "Ao configurar seus próprios endpoints de login e registro, você não precisa habilitar os endpoints padrão, portanto, pode remover as configurações `quarkus.webauthn.enable-login-endpoint` e `quarkus.webauthn.enable-registration-endpoint`."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Thankfully, you can use the link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] bean to handle the WebAuthn-specific part of\n"
"your registration and login endpoints, and focus on your own logic:"
msgstr "Felizmente, você pode usar o bean link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] para lidar com a parte específica do WebAuthn em seus endpoints de registro e login, e focar em sua própria lógica:"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`]\n"
"methods do not set or read the <<configuration-reference,session cookie>>, so you will have to take care\n"
"of it yourself, but it allows you to use other means of storing the user, such as JWT. You can use the\n"
"link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#rememberUser(java.lang.String,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.rememberUser`]\n"
" and link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#logout(io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.logout`]\n"
" methods on the same link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] class if you want to manually set up login cookies."
msgstr "Os métodos link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] não configuram nem leem o <<configuration-reference,cookie de sessão>>, portanto você terá que cuidar disso sozinho, mas ele permite que você use outros meios de armazenar o usuário, como JWT. Você pode usar os métodos link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#rememberUser(java.lang.String,io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.rememberUser`] e link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html#logout(io.vertx.ext.web.RoutingContext)[`WebAuthnSecurity.logout`] na mesma classe link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] se desejar configurar manualmente os cookies de login."

#. type: Title =
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Blocking version"
msgstr "Versão bloqueante"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you're using a blocking data access to the database, you can safely block on the\n"
"link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`] methods,\n"
"with `.await().indefinitely()`, because nothing is async in the `register` and `login` methods, besides the\n"
"data access with your link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`]."
msgstr "Se você estiver usando um acesso a dados bloqueante ao banco de dados, poderá bloquear com segurança nos métodos link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnSecurity.html[`WebAuthnSecurity`], com `.await().indefinitely()`, pois nada é assíncrono nos métodos `register` e `login`, além do acesso a dados com o seu link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`]."

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You will have to add the `@Blocking` annotation on your link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`] class in order for the\n"
"Quarkus WebAuthn endpoints to defer those calls to the worker pool."
msgstr "Você precisará adicionar a anotação `@Blocking` na sua classe link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`] para que os endpoints do Quarkus WebAuthn deleguem essas chamadas para o pool de workers."

#. type: Title =
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Virtual-Threads version"
msgstr "Versão Virtual-Threads"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: gemini
#: _guides/security-webauthn.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You will have to add the `@RunOnVirtualThread` annotation on your link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`] class in order to tell the\n"
"Quarkus WebAuthn endpoints to defer those calls to the worker pool."
msgstr "Você precisará adicionar a anotação `@RunOnVirtualThread` na sua classe link:{webauthn-api}/io/quarkus/security/webauthn/WebAuthnUserProvider.html[`WebAuthnUserProvider`] para instruir os endpoints do Quarkus WebAuthn a delegarem essas chamadas para o pool de workers."

#. type: Title =
